    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-03-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="507"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Director, Office of War Mobilization and Reconversion</hi>
                        (<hi rend="italic">Byrnes</hi>), <hi rend="italic">to the President</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Excerpt]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-08">March 8,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum For the President</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">From: James F. Byrnes</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>At Yalta, the Prime Minister wished to discuss shipping and the British Import
                    Program. <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> and I advised Lord
                    Leathers that the problem was too complicated to be discussed so far away from
                    basic data and that it would have to be resolved in Washington. Leathers
                    accepted this viewpoint and said on several occasions that he would come to the
                    United States at an early date to discuss the shipping situation.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
